      "writtenOn": "2021-06-04T19:30:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is the idea here that the user would use the API like this:\n```\nfor (GlyphRun run in myShapedText.glyph_runs) {\n  context.fillGlyphs(run.glyph_ids, run.positions, run.Font);\n}\n```\nI\u0027m curious if there have been any thoughts around having a `fillGlyphRun` method instead. Is there any advantage to passing the glyphs, positions, and Font separately? Maybe there are other use cases that require this separation that I\u0027m not aware of?",
      "revId": "28f43f512aeaf49ab407f788610cee8e329b4f48",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "323837eb_12ebc852",
        "filename": "experimental/sktext/canvas2d.md",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 25,
      "author": {
        "id": 5649
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-04T20:53:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Could go either way. However, once you start adding in your own notion of \"decorations\", (as I did in my hacky demo textedit.js) I found the need to sometimes only draw a subset of a given Run... which was easy since I could take a slice of the glyphs and positions arrays, and pass those manually.",
      "parentUuid": "dfa7d66a_0bbf227b",
      "revId": "28f43f512aeaf49ab407f788610cee8e329b4f48",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
